  "instructions": [
    "Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the onion and cook until browned, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic and ginger and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the chicken and cook until browned on all sides, about 5-7 minutes.",
    "Add the cumin, cinnamon, paprika, salt, and black pepper. Cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the dried prunes and chicken broth. Bring to a boil, then cover and transfer to the oven.",
    "Bake at 300°F (150°C) for 25-30 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through.",
    "Serve hot over couscous or rice."
